---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="How PerkCommons works" description="How PerkCommons reviews, publishes, and maintains open opportunity data.">
  <section class="container py-14"><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand">How it works</p><h1 class="mt-2 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-semibold">A public index with a visible editorial trail.</h1><p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-muted">PerkCommons makes credible opportunities easier to discover while keeping the data portable, reviewable, and free.</p>
    <ol class="mt-14 grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-md border border-line bg-line md:grid-cols-5">{["Submit", "Screen", "Review", "Publish", "Maintain"].map((step, index) => <li class="bg-white p-5"><span class="text-xs font-semibold text-brand">0{index + 1}</span><p class="mt-3 font-semibold">{step}</p></li>)}</ol>
    <div class="mt-16 grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-2"><section><h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What review means</h2><p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-muted">A moderator identifies a credible source, checks that material eligibility is described, and confirms the destination appears legitimate. This is recorded as a dated source check, not a guarantee.</p></section><section><h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Editorial independence</h2><p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-muted">Payment never purchases factual approval, verification, or removal of a competitor. Sponsored placements are labeled and reviewed under the same evidence standard.</p></section></div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
